It is widely regarded as the 'Manhattan' of Mumbai and it boasts of a spectacular skyline and pricey residential condos. It is also the main financial district of Mumbai and houses most of the financial services and brokerage companiesâboth Indian and international. It is also the location for the Vidhan Bhavan which is the political headquarters of the state of Maharashtra.
